Product: Credit card
Sub-product: General-purpose credit card or charge card
Issue: Advertising and marketing, including promotional offers
Sub-issue: Didn't receive advertised or promotional terms
Consumer complaint narrative: Hello, I got the capital one XXXX credit card in XX/XX/year>. I was told I would be getting a XXXX dollar welcome bonus if I spent over XXXX dollars. I spent that in the first month. It is XXXX and I am still yet to receive it. I called and they claimed I didn't get the reward on my terms & conditions letter. This was extremely deceptive, I would not have applied for the credit card and had the ding my credit score as a result if I had known this. This wasn't a new promo too, you can check credit card articles dated much earlier to know that this card was offering this promo for a long time.

Product: Money transfer, virtual currency, or money service
Credit reporting or other personal consumer reports
Consumer complaint narrative:
Dear OneMain Financial Customer Service, I am writing to formally dispute the reporting of late payments on my OneMain Financial account ( Account Number : XXXX ) for the months of XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXXXX/XX/year>. I believe this information is inaccurate and is causing substantial harm to my creditworthiness. 

Under the Fair Credit Reporting Act ( FCRA ), you are required to report accurate information to the credit bureaus. By continuing to report these late payments, you are in violation of the following FCRA provisions : 1. ** 1681s-2 ( a ) ( 1 ) ( A ) ** Duty of furnishers of information to provide accurate information. 
2. ** 1681i ( a ) ** Procedure in case of disputed accuracy. 

The continued reporting of these inaccuracies has significantly damaged my credit score, affecting my ability to secure loans and resulting in financial loss. If these errors are not corrected, I will have no choice but to seek legal recourse. 

Litigation will not only demand correction of these errors but also compensation for damages incurred. Based on precedent, I estimate the litigation cost for both parties could exceed {$10000.00}, including but not limited to attorney fees, court costs, and potential statutory and punitive damages.

Product: Mortgage
Sub-product: Home equity loan or line of credit (HELOC)
Sub-issue: Trying to communicate with the company to fix an issue while managing or servicing your loan
Consumer complaint narrative:
I reached out on XX/XX/24 after my HELOC was transferred to Shellpoint from SLS. My online portal was showing a monthly payment due that was {$350.00} more than it should have been. I had already made 11 payments on the loan with my previous servicer that were calculated correctly. I was told a ticket was put in a would take 3-5 days. I received no response and have reached out several more times both through customer service and the online portal and still nobody has fixed the issue. They refuse to look and correct the monthly amount due calcuation which is objectively wrong based on my loan document which they have, my prior statements from the past servicer, and a simple calculation given all the loan terms that their own portal confirms. I am getting strung along and they keep " opening tickets '' but I am not being allowed to speak to anyone but Customer Service who can't fix anything. My last payment, sent to the previous loan servicer, was applied fully to the principal in error ( this is proven by looking at my principal balance from the XXXX statement and the current principal balance displayed, and also because my current payoff quote is still calculating interest back through XXXX even though I made my monthly XXXX payment. 

I have a payment due soon and I refuse to pay an inflated amount simply because they made an error and will not change the amount to match my SIGNED LOAN CONTRACT. This is illegal.
Company public response: Company believes it acted appropriately as authorized by contract or law
